The '''Beijing babbler''' ('''''Rhopophilus pekinensis'''''), also known as the '''white-browed Chinese warbler''', '''Chinese hill warbler''', or '''Chinese bush-dweller''', is a species of [[bird]] in the genus ''[[Rhopophilus]]''.<ref name = "ITIS"/> It is now thought to be a close relative of the [[Parrotbill|parrotbills]] and is placed in the family [[Parrotbill|Paradoxornithidae]]; previously, it was placed in the families [[Cisticolidae]], [[Timaliidae]] or [[Sylviidae]]. It is found in northern [[China]] and [[North Korea]], and formerly occurred in [[South Korea]]. The species was [[Species description|first described]] by [[Robert Swinhoe]] in 1868.

